# set base directory
baseDIR = Path("..").resolve()
assert baseDIR.is_dir()

# data directory
dataDIR = "/home/skalevag/Documents/NRC_P8_water_energy_and_sediment/data"
dataDIR = Path(dataDIR)
localDataDIR = baseDIR.joinpath("data")

# station
station_name = "vent"
station_id = 201350  # station id for Vent-Rofental gauging station, as used by HD Tirol
events_version = "automatic_local_minimum_events"

# events
file_events = localDataDIR.joinpath(
    "events_database",
    station_name,
    events_version,
    f"{station_id}_{station_name}_event_metrics.csv",
)

# output directories
resDIR = baseDIR.joinpath("results").joinpath(
    f"{events_version}_{station_name}", "metrics_clustering"
)
if not resDIR.is_dir():
    resDIR.mkdir()

    "SSC_mean_weighted",
]

    event_metrics[f"{col}_log"] = np.log(event_metrics[col])

Decomposition¶

In [13]:
X = training_data.values
np.save(resDIR.joinpath("X"), X)
scaler = preprocessing.StandardScaler()
X_scale = scaler.fit_transform(X)
np.save(resDIR.joinpath("X_scaled"), X_scale)
joblib.dump(scaler, resDIR.joinpath(f"scaler.joblib"))
training_data_scale = pd.DataFrame(
    X_scale, columns=variables, index=training_data.index
)
training_data_scale.to_csv(resDIR.joinpath("training_data_scaled.csv"))

PCA¶

In [14]:
pca = decomposition.PCA()
pca.fit(X_scale)
loadings = pca.components_.T * np.sqrt(pca.explained_variance_)
In [15]:
cum_var_level = 0.8
fig = eval_plot_PCA(pca, cum_var_level=cum_var_level)
selected_components = (
    np.where(np.cumsum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_) > cum_var_level)[0][0] + 1
)
plt.title(f"First {selected_components} components explain >80% of variance")
plt.savefig(resDIR.joinpath("pca_eval_plot.png"))
print(f"Keeping first {selected_components} components")

Keeping first 7 components
In [16]:
pca = decomposition.PCA(n_components=selected_components)
X_reduced = pca.fit_transform(X_scale)
training_data_reduced = pd.DataFrame(
    X_reduced,
    columns=[f"PC{c+1}" for c in range(selected_components)],
    index=training_data.index,
)

pc_df = pd.DataFrame(
    abs(pca.components_),
    columns=variables,
    index=[f"PC{c+1}" for c in range(selected_components)],
)
In [17]:
# save to file
np.save(resDIR.joinpath("X_reduced"), X_reduced)
training_data_reduced.to_csv(resDIR.joinpath("training_data_reduced.csv"))
pc_df.to_csv(resDIR.joinpath("pca_feature_importance_absolute_eigenvector_components.csv"))
joblib.dump(pca, resDIR.joinpath(f"pca.joblib"))

In [19]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(
    nrows=int(np.ceil(selected_components / 2)), ncols=2, figsize=(15, 15), sharex=False
)
ax = ax.ravel()
for i, c in enumerate(pc_df.index):
    sub = pc_df.loc[c].sort_values()
    sub.plot.barh(ax=ax[i],color=[feature_colors[f] for f in sub.index],width=0.8)
    ax[i].set_title(c)
    ax[i].set_xlabel("Absolute value of eigenvector components")
try:
    ax[len(pc_df.index) + 1].axis("off")
except IndexError:
    pass
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig(resDIR.joinpath("pca_feature_importance.png"))
In [20]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=selected_components, ncols=selected_components, figsize=(6*selected_components,6*selected_components),)
for i in range(selected_components):
    for j in range(selected_components):
        if i==j:
            sub = pc_df.iloc[i,:].sort_values()
            sub.plot.barh(ax=ax[j][i],color=[feature_colors[f] for f in sub.index],width=0.8)
            ax[j][i].set_title(f"PC{i+1}")
            ax[j][i].set_xlabel("Absolute value of eigenvector components")
        else:
            plot_variables_in_pca_space(loadings, variables, i+1, j+1, ax=ax[j][i], legend=False, colors=list(feature_colors.values()))
            if i != 0:
                ax[j][i].set_ylabel("")
            if j != selected_components-1:
                ax[j][i].set_xlabel("")
#plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig(resDIR.joinpath("pca_variables_vs_components_all.png"))
